    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>TAX CREDITS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By WENDY GINSBERG</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Ginsberg, Wendy</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New Jersey Assembly appropriations committee approves bill that would provide tax refunds to families that have at least one child and earn less than $20,000 a year (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>More than 280,000 low-income New Jerseyans with jobs would be eligible for state income tax refunds under a bill passed unanimously by the Assembly appropriations committee last week. The bill would provide tax refunds to families that have at least one child and earn less than $20,000 a year. Eligible families would get a check equivalent to 10 percent of their federal income tax credit, and within four years that amount would rise to 20 percent.</p>
        <p>WENDY GINSBERG</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
